    "chunk_text": "4R-1 is relevant. This is a letter written by the Director General of the\n\nWRT/0127/20\n\nPage 49 of 56\n\nDepartment of Archaeology, dated 04.09.2017, to the Director General\n\nof the CCF. Paragraphs 1 and 4 read as follows:\n\n21. According to which, the Director General of Archaeology has informed\n\nthat upon a discussion held with the Minister and the Secretary, it has\n\nbeen decided that the persons who may be recruited to the CCF, upon\n\nbeing so recruited, would be attached to the Department of Archaeology.\n\nFurther it has also been stated by the Director General, in no uncertain\n\nterms, that the said recruitments to the CCF be made in accordance\n\nwith the scheme of recruitment of persons with the requisite\n\nqualifications, as such persons are due to be absorbed to the\n\nDepartment of Archaeology. This, as I see, is a clear holding out by the\n\nDirector General of Archaeology that, in fact, the petitioner, in due\n\ncourse, would be absorbed.\n\n22. The use of the words \u2018attach\u2019 (\u2018\u0d85\u0db1\u0dd4\u0dba\u0dd4\u0d9a\u0dca\u0dad\u2019) and \u2018absorb\u2019 (\u2018\u0d85\u0db1\u0dca\u0dad\u0dad\u0dbb\u0dca\u0d9c\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb \u0dab\u0dba\u2019) in\n\nthis letter is very significant and relevant. \u2018Attach\u2019 is defined in the\n\nBlack\u2019s Law Dictionary (8th Ed.) as follows:\n\n\u201cattach vb. 1. To annex, bind or fasten.\u201d\n\nAs for attachment in the context of employment, it will mean that upon\n\nthe recruitment to the CCF, such persons will, at some point, be annexed\n\nto or taken over by the Department of Archaeology. Then, the word\n\n\u2018absorption\u2019, used in paragraph 4, clearly establishes that the future\n\nattachment to the Department of Archaeology goes beyond a mere\n\n\u2018appointment\u2019. An appointment will contemplate a form of employment\n\nWRT/0127/20\n\nPage 50 of 56\n\nin the first instance. However, \u2018absorption\u2019 will presuppose some form of\n\nappointment with one agency (the CCF) that would be regularised within\n\nthe Department of Archaeology, which would contemplate a form of\n\nmerger between the employment in the CCF and the Department of\n\nArchaeology. According to the Black\u2019s Law Dictionary (8th Ed.),\n\n\u2018absorption\u2019 is defined as follows:"
