    "chunk_text": "Accordingly, I hold that there is no legal impediment for an application seeking intervention to be allowed. Provided that the said party establishes to the satisfaction of Court that the party seeking intervention has sufficient interest and is affected by the relief sought by the Petitioner in a writ application.\n\n5 | P a g e\n\nI wish to cite the following paragraph of the judgment of Justice Priyantha Fernando in the aforesaid Janak Liyanage case.\n\n\u201cHis Lordship Thurairajah J sitting in Court of Appeal considered the decision in the case of Government School of Dental Therapist Association Vs. Director General of Health Service and Others wherein court allowed intervention that, \"Each of the Intervenient Petitioners in the present case cannot be said to be a different \"meddlesome busybody\" or a \"meddlesome interloper\" who does not have a sufficient interest in the pending application. I would therefore adopt the liberalized rules in regard to the standing of a party entitled to seek a remedy to the case of an intervenient who similarly has a sufficient interest in the subject matter of pending writ application and on that basis to permit the intervention.\u201d (Emphasis added)\n\nThe Court of Appeal in the Janak Liyanage case has also cited the following judicial authorities which considered the aspect of intervention in writ applications."
